<p>Pinterest has 619 million monthly active users. 93% of them use the platform to plan purchases. And 97% of the top searches on Pinterest are unbranded, meaning users search for ideas and products without typing a specific company name.</p>
<p>Pinterest for business is fundamentally different from every other social platform. Instagram and TikTok are social networks where people scroll. Pinterest is a visual search engine where people plan. That distinction matters because search intent converts. A user searching "modern kitchen remodel ideas" on Pinterest is actively planning to spend money.</p>
<p>The numbers prove the conversion gap. Pinterest drives 2x more traffic to shopping sites than Facebook. The average Pinterest order value is $58, the highest of any social platform. Pins live for an average of 3.88 months. Instagram posts die in 48 hours, according to <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/pinterest-statistics/">DemandSage</a>.</p>
<p>This guide covers how to set up, optimize, and grow a Pinterest business account. We publish 3,500+ articles across 70+ industries at Stacc, and content-driven traffic strategies are our core focus.</p>
<p><strong>Here is what you will learn:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Why Pinterest outperforms other platforms for website traffic and sales</li>
<li>How Pinterest SEO works (keyword placement, Rich Pins, algorithm signals)</li>
<li>The content strategy that builds compounding traffic over months</li>
<li>Which industries perform best on Pinterest (with data)</li>
<li>How to run Pinterest ads that cost less than Meta or Google</li>
