<p>Rich Pins require a one-time setup: add Open Graph or Schema.org meta tags to your website, then validate through Pinterest's Rich Pin Validator. After validation, all Pins from your domain automatically become Rich Pins.</p>
<h3>Pinterest Algorithm Ranking Factors</h3>
<p>The algorithm evaluates 4 signals:</p>
<p><strong>1. Pin Quality:</strong> Measured by saves, clicks, close-ups, and time spent viewing. High-resolution vertical images (2:3 ratio, 1000x1500px minimum) perform best.</p>
<p><strong>2. Pinner Quality (Account Authority):</strong> Based on posting frequency, engagement rate, account history, and niche consistency. Verified websites boost this score.</p>
<p><strong>3. Relevance:</strong> Pinterest AI scans titles, descriptions, board context, and the linked page content. It also interprets images visually. A photo of a kitchen is categorized as kitchen content even without text keywords.</p>
<p><strong>4. Freshness:</strong> New Pins receive an algorithmic boost in the first few hours. Early engagement in this window determines broader distribution. Fresh URL + fresh image = maximum freshness signal.</p>
<h2>Content Strategy for Pinterest</h2>
<p>Pinterest rewards consistency over virality. Posting 5 to 15 fresh Pins per day is optimal for established accounts. New accounts should start at 3 to 5 per day.</p>
<h3>What Performs Best</h3>
<p><strong>Vertical images</strong> at 2:3 aspect ratio (1000x1500px) outperform all other formats. Text overlays on images increase saves. Clear, bright photography with minimal clutter earns more clicks.</p>
<p><strong>Video Pins</strong> receive distribution priority in home feeds. Short videos (15 to 30 seconds) showing product usage, tutorials, or transformations perform well.</p>
<p><strong>Idea Pins</strong> (multi-page story format) get algorithmic favor. They work for step-by-step tutorials, recipe walk-throughs, and how-to content.</p>
