<p>A single blog post can generate 3 to 5 Pins with different images, different titles, and the same destination URL. Pinterest treats each Pin as a separate piece of content in search results. This is the compounding engine: more Pins = more search surface area.</p>
<h3>Board Strategy</h3>
<p>Organize Pins into topic-specific boards. Each board title should match a search query.</p>
<p><strong>Good board titles:</strong> "Modern Kitchen Remodel Ideas," "Vegan Dinner Recipes," "Wedding Photography Inspiration"</p>
<p><strong>Bad board titles:</strong> "My Favorites," "Stuff I Like," "Inspiration Board"</p>
<p>Create 10 to 15 boards covering your core topics. Add 20 to 30 Pins per board before making them public. A half-empty board signals low quality to the algorithm.</p>
