<h3>Ecommerce on Pinterest</h3>
<p>Ecommerce businesses have a structural advantage. Product Rich Pins show real-time pricing and availability. Shopping Pins link directly to the product page. Collection ads combine a hero image with product tiles.</p>
<p>Pinterest users spend 29% longer viewing shopping content compared to other platforms. Buyable items saved grew 50% year over year, per <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/pinterest-statistics/">DemandSage</a>.</p>
<h3>Service and B2B Businesses</h3>
<p>Pinterest works for service businesses that produce visual or educational content. Interior designers, <a href="/blog/photographer-seo-guide/">photographers</a>, wedding planners, fitness coaches, and nutritionists all perform well.</p>
<p>B2B companies succeed with infographics, data visualizations, and downloadable resources (checklists, templates, guides). The key is creating Pins that link to a <a href="/glossary/landing-page/">landing page</a> with a lead capture form.</p>
