<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>Is Pinterest still relevant for business in 2026?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Pinterest reached 619 million monthly active users in Q4 2025, a 12% increase year over year. Revenue hit $1.319 billion in Q4 2025. Gen Z is the fastest-growing segment at 42% of users. The platform's purchase intent (93% plan purchases) and content longevity (3.88 month average Pin lifespan) make it one of the most cost-effective traffic channels.</p>
<p><strong>How often should I post on Pinterest for business?</strong></p>
<p>New accounts should post 3 to 5 fresh Pins per day. Growing accounts: 5 to 10. Established accounts: 10 to 15. Consistency matters more than volume. Use a scheduling tool to space Pins throughout the day. Irregular posting hurts algorithmic reach.</p>
<p><strong>Do Pinterest Pins show up in Google search results?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Pinterest pages are indexed by Google. Well-optimized Pins with keyword-rich titles and descriptions appear in Google Image search and sometimes in standard search results. Treating Pinterest SEO and <a href="/blog/on-page-seo-guide/">Google SEO</a> as complementary strategies maximizes visibility on both platforms.</p>
<p><strong>Is Pinterest better than Instagram for driving website traffic?</strong></p>
<p>For traffic, yes. Every Pin includes a clickable link. Instagram limits links to the bio. Pinterest Pins live for months. Instagram posts die in hours. Pinterest drives 2x more traffic to shopping sites than Facebook. For brand building and community engagement, Instagram has advantages. The best strategy uses both.</p>
<p><strong>What type of content performs best on Pinterest?</strong></p>
<p>Vertical images (2:3 ratio, 1000x1500px) with text overlays outperform all other formats. Video Pins receive algorithm priority. Idea Pins (multi-page stories) work for tutorials. Product Pins with real-time pricing drive direct sales. Infographics and step-by-step guides earn the most saves.</p>
<p><strong>How much do Pinterest ads cost?</strong></p>
<p>CPC ranges from $0.10 to $1.50. Pinterest ads are 2.3x cheaper per conversion than competing platforms. Start with $500 to $1,000 per month. The unique advantage: organic saves of promoted Pins continue driving traffic after the campaign ends at zero additional cost.</p>
<p>Pinterest is a search engine that happens to look like a social network. Every Pin is a long-lived search result that drives traffic for months. The businesses winning on Pinterest in 2026 treat it with the same keyword research and optimization rigor they apply to Google. Start with 10 boards, 5 Pins per day, and Rich Pins enabled. The compounding effect takes care of the rest.</p>
